 :tx/rationale "Create task: SOUND-NAN-v2: FiniteF64 newtype + NaN elimination in spectral/graph computation. CONTEXT: NaN propagation is the only silent-corruption path in Rust where comparison operators produce wrong results. 40+ call sites in graph.rs can produce NaN via division by zero (PageRank zero-out-degree, spectral gap zero-max-eigenvalue, Phi zero entities). Scattered is_finite() checks are incomplete and unmaintainable. APPROACH: FORMAL-METHODS SOLUTION using type-level NaN prevention. PART 1: FiniteF64 newtype (crates/braid-kernel/src/finite.rs, new file ~150 LOC). (a) pub struct FiniteF64(f64) — private inner, construction only via FiniteF64::new(f: f64) -> Option<FiniteF64> returning None if !f.is_finite(). (b) FiniteF64::zero() -> FiniteF64 and FiniteF64::one() -> FiniteF64 as safe constants. (c) Implement Add, Sub, Mul: always produce FiniteF64 (finite + finite = finite). (d) Implement checked_div: FiniteF64::checked_div(self, rhs: FiniteF64) -> Option<FiniteF64> returning None for division by zero. This is where NaN would originate — the type system forces the caller to handle it. (e) Implement Ord and Eq (SAFE because NaN is excluded). This means FiniteF64 can be used in BTreeMap keys, sorting, and comparison — f64 cannot. (f) Implement PartialOrd<f64> for mixed comparisons during migration. (g) impl From<FiniteF64> for f64 (always safe). (h) Display, Debug, Serialize, Deserialize. PART 2: Migration of spectral metrics (query/graph.rs). Replace f64 return types with FiniteF64 or Option<FiniteF64> in: (a) spectral_decomposition_adaptive() — eigenvalues: Vec<FiniteF64>. Add convergence: bool to return. (b) fiedler() -> Option<FiniteF64> (None for disconnected graphs). (c) cheeger() -> Option<FiniteF64> (None for zero Fiedler value). (d) spectral_gap() -> Option<FiniteF64> (None for zero-max-eigenvalue). (e) page_rank() -> Vec<FiniteF64> (zero-out-degree nodes get 1/N). (f) von_neumann_entropy() -> FiniteF64 (zero eigenvalues contribute 0 to -sum(p*log(p))). (g) ricci_curvature_adaptive() -> Vec<Option<FiniteF64>>. PART 3: Migration of bilateral.rs. All F(S) components use FiniteF64 internally. The FitnessScore struct fields become FiniteF64. The .total field is the weighted sum. All division by spec_count uses checked_div with fallback to FiniteF64::zero(). PART 4: Convergence flag for eigensolver. Jacobi rotation returns (eigenvalues: Vec<FiniteF64>, converged: bool, iterations: usize). If !converged, callers log a warning and can decide to proceed with approximate values or abort. PART 5: Proptest verification. test_finite_spectral_metrics: For any N×N adjacency matrix (N in 1..10, entries drawn from 0.0..1.0 via FiniteF64), all spectral metrics return Some(finite) or None — never panic, never NaN. DEGENERATE CASE TESTS: (a) Empty graph (0 nodes): all metrics return None. (b) Single node: PageRank = 1.0, spectral gap = None. (c) Fully disconnected N nodes: N independent components, Fiedler = 0. (d) Fully connected: well-conditioned, all metrics finite. (e) Star graph: hub PageRank >> leaf. (f) Zero-weight edges: metrics degrade gracefully. ACCEPTANCE: (A) FiniteF64 type exists with construction, arithmetic, and Ord. (B) No f64::NAN can propagate through spectral metrics — type system prevents it. (C) Proptest passes for random adjacency matrices. (D) All 6 degenerate cases tested. (E) Eigensolver returns convergence flag. (F) F(S) components use FiniteF64 internally. (G) No behavior change for well-conditioned inputs. (H) All existing tests pass. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/finite.rs (new), crates/braid-kernel/src/query/graph.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/bilateral.rs. TRACES-TO: INV-BILATERAL-001, INV-QUERY-002."
